Reading the image:

import numpy as np
import cv2
img = cv2.imread('C:/Users/User/Documents/Python Scripts/jerry.jpg')
gray_img = cv2.imread('image.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)


Writing the image:

cv2.imwrite('C:/Users/User/Documents/Python Scripts/jerry.jpg', img)
